OL,3,CJersey Ports want #60 million to turn
OL,4,Cderelict La Folie Inn into hotel
OL,6,FThe Ports of Jersey have revealed
OL,7,Ftheir hopes for the future of La Folie
OL,8,FInn, which has remained closed and
OL,9,Fderelict for more than 20 years.
OL,11,FThe listed building ceased trading as
OL,12,Fa pub in 2004 and Ports became the
OL,13,Flandlord a decade ago.
OL,15,FThey hope to finally repurpose the
OL,16,Fbuilding and the surrounding area into
OL,17,Fa hotel, if they can find a
OL,18,F"development partner" and at least #60
OL,19,Fmillion in investment.
